Password Protect for Croogo
------------------------------
Password protect with htaccess/htpasswd your main web directory.

This plugin is useful if you need to password protect the entire site for client previews.


How to use
------------------------------
- Log in to admin panel
- Go to Extensions > Plugins page
- Upload the zip file (available here)
- Click on tick/cross icon of 'Password Protect' for activating or deactivating the plugin


Notes
------------------------------
- Hashed passwords don't generate correctly on Apache running on Windows
- Make sure .htaccess and .htpasswd exist and are writable by Apache
